<font color="#FF0000">WHOM DO WE REMEMBER THIS DAY?</font><br>
<tt>Tue May 27  2:13:18 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
We can, and do, argue about the politics behind wars.  But Memorial Day is a day to set all that &quot;stuff&quot; behind and simply remember those who are not here to voice their opinions.  <br><br>
People like <br><br>
Charlie King, <br>
Dave Davidson and <br>
Paul Jenkins, <br><br>
people like <br><br>
Michael Dean, <br>
Luther Davis and <br>
James Plieman,<br><br>
people like<br><br>
William Pitsenbarger,<br>
Steven Adams and<br>
Robert Berry,<br><br>
people like<br><br>
James Locker,<br>
Harry Cohen and<br>
William Pruett,<br><br>
people like<br><br>
William Sutton,<br>
James Thomas and<br>
Raymond Crow,<br><br>
people like<br><br>
Raymond Wagner,<br>
Allen Avery, <br>
James Prose and<br>
William Pearson,<br><br>
people like these people, USAF Pararescuemen who lost their lives in Vietnam while conducting combat rescue missions, are the ones we need to remember on this day.  <br><br>

<p><code>-- searat@sorcom.com  (John C. Ratliff) </code><p>


